<H2><U>
<a name="figures">Important Columbian Mythological Figures</a>
</u></H2>

<B><img src="vinesmall.jpg"><font size=4><I><U><A href="http://www.native-languages.org/west-coast-coyote.htm">Coyote</a></font></U></B></I>: 
The trickster hero of the Columbian and other Interior Salish tribes.
Coyote is foolish and boastful, and so Columbian stories about him are often humorous in nature; 
however, he is a well-meaning creature who usually acts for the good of humankind.

<H2><U>
<a name="tribes">Columbian Indian Stories</a>
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><B><A HREF="
http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/CreationoftheFirstIndians-Chelan.html
">Creation of the First Indians</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Chelan (Moses-Columbia) legend about the creation of man.
<BR>

